China's cutting of the reserve ratio 
requirements for banks may signal a more aggressive monetary 
easing. Three high-ranking JPMorgan executives are reported to 
be leaving the bank in the fallout of its $2 billion dollar 
trading loss. The political deadlock in Greece continues with 
no agreement on a unity government. Bloomberg's Susan Li 
reports. (Source: Bloomberg)  Running Time: 01:24
 